29/08/2003
TIRANA, Albania -- Government officials said Wednesday (27 August) that the Kosovo issue has entered a new stage. 
According to Deputy Foreign Minister Luan Hajdaraga, the fact that it is being discussed at all represents a big step forward. 
He added that Kosovo's participation in the EU summit in Thessaloniki proves the province is getting more recognition worldwide. 
For his part, Albanian President Alfred Moisiu said that regional co-operation efforts should bring Tirana and Belgrade closer. 
(KosovaLive, BBC, B92 - 27/08/03)
